Version 1.0.0

Release Date: December 2025
Project: LLM-Based Database Management System
Institution: Eskisehir Technical University
Department: Electrical and Electronics Engineering

This is the initial production release of the LLM-Based DBMS, developed as part of the 2025-2026 Design Project and funded by TUBITAK 2209-A.

Key Features:
- Natural Language to SQL translation using LLMs
- Multi-provider LLM support (OpenAI, Anthropic)
- Advanced SQL safety validation
- Role Based Access Control (RBAC)
- JWT authentication
- Prometheus metrics and structured logging
- Docker and Kubernetes deployment support
- Comprehensive API documentation

Team:
- Derya Umut Kulali (Principal Investigator)
- Anil Aydin (Research Team Member)
- Sila Alhan (Research Team Member)

Academic Advisor:
- Mehmet Fidan

